Before we solve ANY grid DP

There are only 4 questions.

1. What is my state?

Usually

dp[i][j]

means

Answer till cell (i,j)

or

Answer starting from cell (i,j)

depending on the question.

2. From where can I come?

For every cell ask

"Who can reach me?"

Example

□ ← □ ← □
↑
□ ← □ ← □
↑
□ ← □ ← □

If movement is only right/down,

to reach

(i,j)

we came from

(i-1,j)

or

(i,j-1)

That's your recurrence.

3. Base Case

Usually

(0,0)

or

last row

or

last column

depending on the problem.

4. Fill order

If recurrence depends on

up
left

then fill

top → bottom
left → right

If recurrence depends on

down
right

then fill backwards.

Everything depends on dependencies.

Pattern you'll see again and again

Every grid DP is basically

for(i)
{
    for(j)
    {
        dp[i][j]=something
    }
}

Nested loops.

Nothing magical.
